MongoAL operate with streams. It is a list of primitive N>=0 types.

Primitive types: numbers, strings, booleans...

Streams can be created from Primitive types, but also processing the next auxiliary types:

Trees (as JSON objects): can contain primitives, trees, and arrays
Arrays (of primitives, trees, and other arrays)

Operations:
	- Numbers: arithmetic, comparison (return true/false)
	- Strings: concat, substring, search (with regexp?)
	- Bools: and/or/not/xor
	- Array: Add/remove elements. convert to stream
	- Trees: add/remove elements, substitute elements
	
	
	

